AUDIO: 'week, we have a super useful update from ComfyUI. Here they introduce something called dynamic VRAM, which automatically manages your computer\'s VRAM or video memory more intelligently. In the past,'

[13:46] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'you would need to load all the models into memory at once, which would often cause crashes or force you to use lower settings. So for dynamic VRAM, instead of just loading everything at once, it loads and unloads parts of the AI model'

[13:59] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'only when needed during generation. So this actually saves you a lot of VRAM and allows you to use much bigger models or generate higher resolution generations on the same GPU. Plus it reduces out of memory errors. It also'

[14:13] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'makes the generation speed faster. So here is the execution time using 1.2 and an RTX 5060. The red bars are without this new dynamic VRAM and you can see'

